@blaueck Tried Python 3.6.6, but now I get the error below. Changing bazel from 17 to 15 doesn't help.

c:\users\joey\_bazel_joey\juz2ghmw\execroot\org_tensorflow\external\eigen_archive\eigen\src/Core/arch/CUDA/Half.h(212): error: more than one instance of overloaded function "__hadd" matches the argument list:
            function "__hadd(int, int)"
            function "__hadd(__half, __half)"
            argument types are: (const Eigen::half, const Eigen::half)

Related to #19198

What compute capability are you specifying I wonder? I'm specifying 7.5 which is the RTX's compute level.

I tried both yes and no to "override strong inline eigen" stuff, no change.

body:
@blaueck Tried Python 3.6.6, but now I get the error below. Changing bazel from 17 to 15 doesn't help.

```
c:\users\joey\_bazel_joey\juz2ghmw\execroot\org_tensorflow\external\eigen_archive\eigen\src/Core/arch/CUDA/Half.h(212): error: more than one instance of overloaded function "__hadd" matches the argument list:
            function "__hadd(int, int)"
            function "__hadd(__half, __half)"
            argument types are: (const Eigen::half, const Eigen::half)
```

Related to https://github.com/tensorflow/tensorflow/issues/19198

What compute capability are you specifying I wonder? I'm specifying 7.5 which is the RTX's compute level.

I tried both yes and no to "override strong inline eigen" stuff, no change.
